description: Little friend got trapped in an orange juice Tetra pak, then found itself in the mouth of an unsuspecting human who took a big gulp of juice. Human thought fast and scooped it out of his mouth but didn't know what to do next. I took over I gave it a place to dry out, recover and groom. It became clear after a while that it needed a little gentle attending with a damp napkin to get its wings unstuck. It climbed up my arm and kept busy undoing the sticky pickle it had gotten into. After an hour it was in full flying form and flew away, presumably to rejoin the hive. Happy ending!

description:
Abeja europea o abeja melífera occidental
La abeja europea (Apis mellifera) es probablemente una de las especies de abejas melíferas más populares y fue clasificada por Carl Nilsson Linnaeus en 1758. Existen hasta 20 especies reconocidas y es originaria de Europa, África y Asia, aunque actualmente se ha extendido en todos los continentes, exceptuando en la Antártida. [1]

description: On Nolina interrata male flowers
On Nolina interrata male flowers

Hay muchas de esta abejitas pequeñas en mi jardin, y creo que Son probablemente (ceratina arizonensis). Dos están chupando néctar de mi Algodoncillo de hoja delgada (asclepias fascicularis) 😁💖❤️😊☺️

There are quite lots of them flying around my pollinator garden, I think they are Arizona small carpenter bees. But I’m not sure.

Two of them were sipping nectar from the flowers of our narrow leaf milkweed 😁💖❤️😊☺️
